As a first step of the two-phase parallel rectangle-splitting approach the boundaries of the Pareto front are calculated by solving




zT=lexminx∈X{z1(x),z2(x):z(x)∈R((−∞,∞),(−∞,∞))}



and




zB=lexminx∈X{z2(x),z1(x):z(x)∈R((−∞,∞),(−∞,∞))}



in parallel (Fig 6A). Then, the search space within R(zT,zB) is evenly constraint based on boundary conditions enforced w.l.o.g. on z1 (Fig 6B). The boundaries are calculated for a predefined number of constraints m with:




τiz1=z1T+i∙(z1B−z1T)mwith1≤i≤m.
